EXTRACTED VALUE: I can see that some fans will gain enjoyment, and those gamers tired of the norm, but for my tastes, the appeal of the game was lost pretty early on.
Given the subject matter, Kane & Lynch never had a chance of being a fun game, but it had every chance of being a good one. It's not.
While almost every facet of this game is atrocious, there is a sort of charm that EDF carries that has so far been unseen on the platform.
If you absolutely must get your hands on a next-generation RPG now, give it a shot, but don't be surprised if these Arms feel weak.
N3 is quite a looker, but there's not much under the surface.
